The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization of social welfare, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of facility location games as an example suggests that the paper may also be relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses randomized mechanisms, which are often studied in machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG). Finally, the concept of exchanging outcomes may be relevant to social networks and online marketplaces (cs.SI).
